title.narrative: LB - Cultural Heritage and Urban Dev.

description.narrative: The Project Development Objectives are: (a) to create the conditions for increased local economic development and enhanced quality of life in the historic centers of five main secondary cities; and (b) to improve the conservation and management of Lebanon's built cultural heritage.

condition.narrative: Finance Agreement :L.A. Art. IV, Section 4.01. (a) | Description :Annual audit reports of project accounts and SOEs are preparedand submitted in English by independent auditors acceptable to the Bank within six months of the end of each fiscal year. |Frequency :Yearly

Finance Agreement :L.A. Art. IV, Section 4.01. (b) | Description :Documentation to support expenditures financed under SOEs orotherwise will be maintained in English by CDR and made available for review by Bank supervision missions. | Frequency :Quarterly

Finance Agreement :L.A. Schedule II, Section 2 A (1) | Description :The Borrower shall monitor and evaluate the progress of theProject and shall prepare and furnish to the Bank a Report covering theperiod of one calendar semester and furnished to the Banknot later than one month after the end of the period covered by the Report. | Frequency :Yearly

Finance Agreement :L.A. Schedule II, Section 2 A (2) | Description :The report on the execution of the Project and the related planrequired pursuant to Section 5.08 (c) of the General Conditions shall be furnished to the Bank not later than (6) months after theClosing Date. | Due Date :30-Jun-2016 (changed to 30-Jun-2017 due to 1 year project extension)

Finance Agreement :L.A. Schedule II, Section II B (2) | Description :The Borrower shall prepare and furnish to the Bank not laterthan (45) days after the end of each calendar quarter, interim unaudited financial reports for the Project cover the quarter, inform and substance satisfactory to the Bank. | Frequency :Quarterly

Finance Agreement :L.A. Schedule II, Section II B (3) | Description :The Borrower shall furnish to the Bank audited FinancialStatements covering a period of one fiscal year of the Borrower not later than (6) months after the end of such period. | Frequency:Yearly

Finance Agreement :P.A. Art.II, Section 2.01. (b) | Description :The PMU (CDR) will also prepare and submit an ImplementationCompletion Report to the Bank within six months of the closing date ofthe Bank loan. | Due Date :30-Jun-2016 (changed to30-Jun-2017 due to 1 year project extension)

Finance Agreement :P.A. Schedule II, para. 2 | Description :CDR shall furnish to the Bank semi-annual reports during the periodcommencing on October 30, 2004, and ending on April 30 of each year. | Frequency :Yearly

Finance Agreement :P.A. Schedule II, para. 3 | Description :furnish, by April 30 of each year semi-annual reports on the results ofhe implementation of the Resettlement Policy Framework and Action Plan. | Frequency :Yearly

Finance Agreement :P.A. Schedule II, para.1 (b) | Description :CDR will maintain the Project Management Unit and MIUs establishedfor the project with staffing, terms of reference, and qualifications satisfactory to the Bank. | Frequency :Quarterly

Finance Agreement :P.A. Section I, D (3) | Description :CDR shall furnish to the Bank semi annual reports ending on April 30 ofyear until completion of the Project, describing the progress achieved in the implementation of the Project, including findings andrecommendations, in connection with the EMP. | Frequency :Yearly

Finance Agreement :P.A. Section I, D (4) | Description: CDR shall furnish to the Bank, by each year until completion of theProject, quarterly reports on the results of activities relatedto the RPF and RAP; and shall furnish to the Bank, upon completionof the Project, an assessment, on basis of terms of reference acceptable to the Bank, on the fulfillment of the provisions of therelevant RAPs. | Due Date: 31-Dec-2015 (changed to 31-Dec-2016 due to 1 year project extension)

Finance Agreement :P.A. Section II, A (1) | Description :CDR shall furnish to the Bank, Project Reports covering one calendarsemester, not later than (1) month after the end of the periodcovered for incorporation and forwarding by the Borrower to the Bankof the overall Project Report. | Frequency :Yearly

Finance Agreement :P.A. Section II, A (2) | Description :CDR shall provide to the Borrower not later than May 30, 2016, forincorporation in the report referred to in Section 5.08 (c) of the General Conditions all such information as the Borrower or theBank shall reasonably request for the purposes of that Section. | Due Date :30-May-2016 (changed to 30-May-2017 due to 1 yearproject extension)
